  "description": [
    "20 BLACK GIVES VIEWS ON ALIEN QUESTION Alabaman Holds Immigration Restriction Is Right of America If the movement for repeal of the national origins immigration plan is continued Senator Black Democrat of Alabama will press for a vote on the bill he recently introduced to restrict all immigration for a period of five years beginning July 1 1930 it was in dicated yesterday Senator Black believes the United States has the right to stop all immi gration as well as to select the future citisenshlp of the country on any basis which the people of America may see fit to adopt Issue Called Simple Last year according to the Alabama Senator 37765 Mexicans were legally admitted into the United States Senator Black outlined his views on the immigration question in a radio talk Friday night The recent agitation for a repeal of the national origins method of select ing immigrants has caused the eyes of the thoughtful people of this country to focus upon our immigration policy Senator Black declared The issue in this question is simple Our Government has adopted a policy of restricted immigration from Euro pean countries while permitting unre stricted immigration from Canada Mexico and South"
